Journal Story: Just starting my collection of gear, studying trail literature, and doing short trips.
Just thought I'd share a pic from Old Rag. It was beautiful!

Hello there, 
I had my first Trail Days experience this year. Wow! It was crazy. I've met bunches of crazy, cool peoples. A few stinky ones too.  Can't wait 'til next year! I've been enjoying as much of the green tunnel as work will allow me to. Until next time.. have a good day.

Putting some miles on these feet and getting familiar with my gear.   Should start doing some longer section hikes soon.. when work allows. Just enjoying the evening cricket serenade! Y'all have a good night!

Had a beautiful hike today in Shenandoah National Park. It was a nice, cold, and sunny morning. The trail was covered with snow, over a foot in some places. It made for an interesting hike. Several icy spots tested my balance. The views were totally spectacular! Lots of birds and deer to watch. Overall, had an awesome day! Hopeful that tomorrow will be just as nice. Happy trails!
